# No AI commit attribution (HARD RULE)

This is a **non-negotiable** project rule for every AI agent (Cursor, Claude,
Copilot, ChatGPT, Gemini, or any other).

## Forbidden

- Adding `Co-authored-by:` / `Co-Authored-By:` trailers for any AI
- Examples that must never appear:
  - `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>`
  - `Co-Authored-By: Claude … <noreply@anthropic.com>`
  - Any Copilot / ChatGPT / Gemini / OpenAI co-author line
- Setting `GIT_AUTHOR_*` / `GIT_COMMITTER_*` to an AI identity
- Leaving an auto-injected AI trailer in a commit that gets pushed

## Required

- Commits use **only** the human user's configured git identity
- Prefer `git commit-tree` (or an equivalent path that cannot be injected) when
  the environment is known to append Cursor/Claude trailers on `git commit`
- If a trailer was already created: rewrite the message **before** push
- Repo hooks under `scripts/git-hooks/` strip/reject AI trailers — do not
  disable them

## Why

GitHub maps AI co-author emails (e.g. `cursoragent@cursor.com`) to public bot
accounts and lists them as repo contributors. That is unacceptable for this
project.
